Third-party dependencies and their licenses:

- paramiko (LGPL-2.1) - SSH library.
  Source: https://github.com/paramiko/paramiko
  LGPL-2.1 requires that modifications to the library itself be released under
  the same license. Using paramiko as an unmodified dependency in an MIT project
  is permitted; the LGPL applies only to paramiko's own source code.

- pycades (no license declared) - CryptoPro CAdES interface wrapper for Linux.
  Source: https://github.com/KirillOgleznev/pycades
  This package wraps proprietary CryptoPro CSP libraries. Its use is subject to
  CryptoPro's licensing terms. Not distributed with this software.

- CryptoPro CSP / CAdESCOM (proprietary) - Digital signature provider.
  Required for Chestny Znak API authentication. Must be licensed separately.
  https://www.cryptopro.ru/products/csp
